[recto] Ad [Addendum] Martinsfest. See drawings attributed to Abraham Govaerts 1589-1626 of the same subject in Stockholm, National Museum Dutch & Flemish Drawings, Stockholm 1953, N° 115 (pl. 20) not a feast, but St. Martin with beggars and on the side a man drinking. cf. painting signed and dated 1626 in Brussels (Yvonne Thiéry in Bull. des Musées R. des Beaux-Arts, Bruxelles, December 1952, p. 135ff; [verso] See also Denucé, Inventar & De Maeyer, Albrecht & Isabella inventory.

column4: <content>[recto] Ad [Addendum] Martinsfest. See drawings attributed to Abraham Govaerts 1589-1626 of the same subject in Stockholm, National Museum Dutch & Flemish Drawings, Stockholm 1953, N° 115 (pl. 20) not a feast, but St. Martin with beggars and on the side a man drinking. cf. painting signed and dated 1626 in Brussels (Yvonne Thiéry in Bull. des Musées R. des Beaux-Arts, Bruxelles, December 1952, p. 135ff; [verso] See also Denucé, Inventar & De Maeyer, Albrecht & Isabella inventory.</content>
